NAME
	./corewar - the "arena" in which champions will be executed (virtual machine)

SYNOPSIS
	./corewar [OPTION] [[-n number] champion1.cor] ...

DESCRIPTION

	-dump N
		at the end of N of execution, dump the memory on standard output
		and quit the game; N must be non-negative integer
	
	-v N
		suppress "live" and "aff" instructions output; verbosity mode with
		N equals:
		1 - translate instructions into assembly language
		2 - add description to mode 1
		3 - show checkups
		4 - (1 + 3) mode
		5 - (2 + 3) mode

	-n number
		set the number of the next player; must be [1..4] without repetition

AUTHOR
	Writen by domurdoc